iA year ago, to simultaneously browse webpages and write codes on my		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iArch Linux
installation and use Windows to run tasks infeasible on		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iLinux (such as gaming),		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
1I tried GPU passthrough on my Lenovo R720 gaming laptop	/en/article/modify-computer/laptop-intel-nvidia-optimus-passthrough.lantian/	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i.
But since that laptop has an Optimus MUXless architecture (as		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imentioned in that
post), its dedicated GPU doesn't have output ports,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iand the integrated GPU is in
charge of all the displays. Therefore,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
isevere limitations exist for that setup,
and I eventually gave up on		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iit.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iBut now, I've purchased a new laptop. The HDMI output port on this		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ilaptop is
directly connected to its NVIDIA dedicated graphics card, or		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iin other words, it
has an Optimus MUXed architecture. Since there is a		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iway to make the virtual
machine aware of a "monitor on the dedicated		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iGPU", most functionalities work
normally. I am finally able to create		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ia GPU passthrough setup that works
long-term.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
