iPassthrough Keyboard & Mouse Operations		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThe latest Looking Glass can relay keyboard and mouse events reliably		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
inow. These
steps are kept for reference only.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThe relay of the keyboard and mouse in Looking Glass isn't very		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
istable, as
misses of operation can happen from time to time.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iTherefore, if you want to play
some games in the VM, you need a more		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ireliable way to pass your keyboard and
mouse into the VM.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iWe have two options: letting Libvirt capture the keyboard and mouse		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ievents or
simply pass your keyboard and mouse into the VM.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Capturing Keyboard and Mouse Events.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- On Linux, all keyboard and mouse operations are passed to the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
idesktop
environment via the `evdev` (or `Event Device`) framework.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iLibvirt can
capture your operations and pass them to the VM. In		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iaddition, Libvirt can
switch the control between the host and the VM		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iwhenever you press Left Ctrl
and the Right Ctrl, so you can operate on		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iboth the host and the VM with one
keyboard-mouse combo.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- First run `ls -l /dev/input/by-path` on the host to see your present		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i`evdev`
devices. I have these ones for example:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Those with `event-mouse` are mouses, and the `event-kbd` ones are		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ikeyboards.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Then, run `virsh edit Windows` to edit the VM config. Add these into		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ithe
`<devices>` section:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Start the VM, and you should notice that your keyboard and mouse		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iaren't
working on the host. They're captured by the VM. Press Left		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iCtrl + Right Ctrl
to return control to the host. Press again to		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
icontrol the VM.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Now we can disable the keyboard and mouse relay of Looking Glass.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iCreate
`/etc/looking-glass-client.ini` with the following content:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
